.TH VAULTWM 1 "2024-01-01" "VaultOS" "VaultOS Manual"
.SH NAME
vaultwm \- VaultOS window manager
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B vaultwm
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B vaultwm
is a lightweight, Fallout-themed window manager for X11 with Pip-Boy-style
status bar. It features tiling and floating layouts, workspace support, and
keyboard-driven navigation.
.SH KEY BINDINGS
.TP
.B Mod4 + Enter
Launch terminal
.TP
.B Mod4 + D
Launch application launcher
.TP
.B Mod4 + Q
Close focused window
.TP
.B Mod4 + T
Toggle layout (Tiling → Floating → Monocle)
.TP
.B Mod4 + F
Toggle floating for current window
.TP
.B Mod4 + 1-9
Switch to workspace 1-9
.TP
.B Mod4 + H/J/K/L
Navigate windows (vim-style)
.TP
.B Mod4 + Arrow Keys
Navigate windows
.TP
.B Mod4 + Left Click
Move window (makes it floating)
.TP
.B Mod4 + Right Click
Resize window (makes it floating)
.PP
Mod4 is typically the Super/Windows key.
.SH CONFIGURATION
Runtime configuration file:
.I ~/.config/vaultwm/config
.PP
Compile-time configuration:
.I /usr/share/vaultwm/config.h
.SH IPC
VaultWM supports IPC via named pipe:
.I ~/.config/vaultwm/vaultwm_ipc
.PP
Send commands by writing to the FIFO:
.IP
echo "focus_next" > ~/.config/vaultwm/vaultwm_ipc
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/vaultwm/config
Runtime configuration file
.TP
.I ~/.config/vaultwm/vaultwm_ipc
IPC named pipe
.TP
.I /usr/share/vaultwm/config.h
Compile-time configuration header
